- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with modeling phonetic durations using deep neural networks, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP).
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with phonetic durations, which is a sound-related feature.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep neural networks for modeling.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper mentions the influence of factors such as speaking rate and pre-pausal lengthening on phonetic durations, which could be related to social and communication networks.
- cs.SD (Signal Processing) is another possible category as the paper deals with analyzing speech signals to predict phonetic durations.
